  "text": "Interestingly, we do not see any significant horizontal structuring within deeper vertical zones. However, within the upper littoral (i.e., a zone typically extending from a water depth of 0 to 3 m), a strong horizontal structure is evident. One eco-zone (\"non-SE upper littoral zone\") comprises all shallow water gastropod communities from the northeastern, northern, western, and southwestern parts of the lake. Three additional eco-zones can be found in the southeastern upper littoral (\"SE upper littoral zones 1-3\"). This area, comprising major spring fields within the lake, has long been known for its high degree of point-endemism [CITATION_1] ; also see Hauffe et al., 2011 Fig. 3a for compositional similarities among these communities).",
